04859nam a22008295i 9783110197402DE-B159720221201113901.0m|||||o||d||||||||cr || ||||||||221201t20082004gw     fo  d z      eng d  a(OCoLC)853259856  a97831101974027 a10.1515/97831101974022doi  a(DE-B1597)32211  a(OCoLC)816881134  aDE-B1597bengcDE-B1597erda0 aeng  agwcDE 4aP291.3aP291.3.L43 2004 7aLAN0090002bisacsh04a4151 aLechner, Winfried, eauthor.4aut4http://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/aut10aEllipsis in Comparatives /cWinfried Lechner. 1aBerlin ;aBoston : bDe Gruyter Mouton, c[2008] 4c©2004  a1 online resource (285 p.)  atextbtxt2rdacontent  acomputerbc2rdamedia  aonline resourcebcr2rdacarrier  atext filebPDF2rda0 aStudies in Generative Grammar [SGG] ,x0167-4331 ;v7200tFrontmatter -- tContents -- tChapter 1. Introduction -- tChapter 2. Comparative Deletion -- tChapter 3. Comparative Ellipsis -- tChapter 4. Comparative Coordination -- tChapter 5. Conclusion -- tBackmatter0 arestricted accessuhttp://purl.org/coar/access_right/c_16ecfonline access with authorization2star  aGenerative analyses of comparatives traditionally include two construction specific ellipsis operations, Comparative Deletion and Comparative Ellipsis. Drawing from a wide array of new data, the present monograph develops a novel, directly semantically interpretable analysis of comparatives which does not require reference to designated deletion processes. On the one hand, Comparative Deletion is reinterpreted in terms of overt movement of the degree predicate. The resulting head-raising analysis contributes to an understanding of various puzzles for comparatives related to binding, locality and the influence of word-order variation on the interpretation and size of the ellipsis site. On the other hand, it is argued that Comparative Ellipsis can entirely be subsumed under standardly sanctioned ellipsis operations such as Gapping, Right Node Raising and Across-the-Board-movement. In addition, the study presents arguments for an ellipsis analysis of phrasal comparatives (such as Millhouse saw more movies than Bart). Empirical support for this conception derives, among others, from the complex interdependencies between ellipsis and serialization in English and German, and the binding properties of remnants inside the comparative complement. The study is directed towards readers interested in formal syntax and the syntax/semantics interface.  aIssued also in print.  aMode of access: Internet via World Wide Web.  aIn English.0 aDescription based on online resource; title from PDF title page (publisher's Web site, viewed 01. Dez 2022) 0aComparison (Grammar). 0aGrammar, Comparative and generalxEllipsis. 0aGrammar, Comparative and generalxSyntax. 4aSyntax. 7aLANGUAGE ARTS & DISCIPLINES / Linguistics / General.2bisacsh08iTitle is part of eBook package:dDe GruytertDGBA Linguistics and Semiotics 2000 - 2014z9783110636970oZDB-23-DLS08iTitle is part of eBook package:dDe GruytertDe Gruyter Mouton Backlist 2000-2015z978311074296108iTitle is part of eBook package:dDe GruytertE-BOOK GESAMTPAKET / COMPLETE PACKAGE 2008z9783110212129oZDB-23-DGG08iTitle is part of eBook package:dDe GruytertE-BOOK PACKAGE ENGLISH LANGUAGES TITLES 2008z978311021213608iTitle is part of eBook package:dDe GruytertE-BOOK PAKET LINGUISTIK UND LITERATURWISSENSCHAFT  2008z9783110209457oZDB-23-DGA0 cprintz978311018118040uhttps://doi.org/10.1515/978311019740240uhttps://www.degruyter.com/isbn/9783110197402423Coveruhttps://www.degruyter.com/document/cover/isbn/9783110197402/original  a978-3-11-021213-6  E-BOOK PACKAGE ENGLISH LANGUAGES TITLES 2008b2008  a978-3-11-074296-1  De Gruyter Mouton Backlist 2000-2015c2000d2015  aEBA_BACKALL  aEBA_CL_LS  aEBA_DGALL  aEBA_EBACKALL  aEBA_EBKALL  aEBA_ECL_LS  aEBA_EEBKALL  aEBA_ESSHALL  aEBA_SSHALL  aGBV-deGruyter-alles  aPDA11SSHE  aPDA13ENGE  aPDA17SSHEE  aPDA5EBK  aZDB-23-DGAb2008